      <p>Where this kettle stands out is repeatability under normal life constraints. On paper, many models offer similar controls. In real routines — early mornings, interrupted brews, switching between recipes — the Stagg EKG stays predictable. That makes it easier to diagnose recipe issues quickly because your kettle variable is stable.</p>
      <p>It also fits “one good cup, then another” workflows well. If you brew for yourself and one other person, hold behavior and fast control adjustments save time while preserving consistency. For brewers tracking light-roast recipes where temperature shifts matter, this can reduce avoidable cup-to-cup swings.</p>
      <p>The tradeoff is cost. If your grinder is still entry level, budget may be better spent on grind quality first. But once your grinder and scale are already strong, this kettle is a meaningful quality-of-life and consistency upgrade.</p>
