      <p>Its value shows up in practical routines. The 1.0L volume is useful when you brew multiple cups, and the controls are simple enough for households where more than one person makes coffee. You are not paying for flashy extras; you are paying for baseline precision and repeatability.</p>
      <p>For many buyers, this is the best “balanced setup” choice because it leaves budget for a better grinder, fresh filters, or a responsive scale. In terms of cup quality improvement per dollar, that systems approach usually beats overspending on a single piece of gear.</p>
      <p>It does not feel as refined as top-tier models, and stream feel may be less polished in very slow pours. Still, for value-focused electric brewing, it remains a strong recommendation.</p>
